  <span class="prop-types">FLEXIBILITY</span>
  <br><br>
 
  <p>
    Flexibility of a racket refers to how stiff the shaft is.<br><br>
    The stiffness of a racketâ€™s shaft influences the racket stroke and recovery time of a player and thus is an important point of consideration when choosing a racket.
    <br><br>
    Flexible rackets are more lenient towards slower shuttle strikes but increases recovery time.
    <br><br>
    Thus in conclusion, 
stiff rackets recovers faster but requires faster power generation and is thus used by pros and experienced players while flexible rackets are recommended for beginners .

  </p>
